Avira (Free) detects 2 TR/Dropper.Gen entries in hidden directory's after install. You can install though (at own risk)  since these 'problems' were easely recovered. Just be sure you disconnect from internet completely during install of this app and have your virusscanner updated and configured in the most safe mode (scanning hidden objects e.g.) and perform a COMPLETE scan after install of the app. Also perform a 'Spybot Search & Destroy'-scan. In this feature you can also select a nice tool that shows which programs start up with your system. Clicking on a entry will immediately show whether it's a thread or not and you can delete it right away: http://www.safer-networking.org/index2.html
